snippet.textDisplay: Really great to see this MR2 basically being fully restored. Both the AW11 and the SW20 are two of the most enjoyable and rewarding cars you could find yourself driving. But I'll never forget the first time I drove an SW20, because I instantly bonded with it, like I'd been driving it for years. Within a few minutes of getting in the car I just understood it, and I had no fears about kicking the clutch and getting the tail out around some tight roads. Even with it's quirks, never has a car felt more "right" to me to drive than an SW20, especially after only a few minutes in drivers seat. I always tell people if they have the chance to own or drive an SW20, you just HAVE to do it.

snippet.textDisplay: With stock CT20B (ST205 turbo) and GEN1 3SGTE I got ~200kW at 4 wheels (16psi). The biggest problem is that CT20B would overboost without factory exhaust. I even completely removed wastegate valve assembly and ran without downpipe and still made 1bar boost at 5000rpm (tried porting the wastegate without any success). The only way I solved this is by using a sandwich plate with 2 external wastegates hanging off it.
snippet.textOriginal: With stock CT20B (ST205 turbo) and GEN1 3SGTE I got ~200kW at 4 wheels (16psi). The biggest problem is that CT20B would overboost without factory exhaust. I even completely removed wastegate valve assembly and ran without downpipe and still made 1bar boost at 5000rpm (tried porting the wastegate without any success). The only way I solved this is by using a sandwich plate with 2 external wastegates hanging off it.

snippet.textDisplay: The 5th injector in the inlet manifold is the cold start injector (electronic equivalent of a choke), this operated: during cranking, when the temperature was low enough, and only for a limited time ( 8 seconds from memory). It's a Bosch system. There will be a cold start injector switch in the cooling jacket that cuts out this injector if the engine is already warm. You shouldn't use a hose clamp on pushlock fitting as the barbs are much sharper and will cut into the hose leading to premature failure, I have experienced this. Make sure you use the correct hose.
snippet.textOriginal: The 5th injector in the inlet manifold is the cold start injector (electronic equivalent of a choke), this operated: during cranking, when the temperature was low enough, and only for a limited time ( 8 seconds from memory). It's a Bosch system. There will be a cold start injector switch in the cooling jacket that cuts out this injector if the engine is already warm.
